# Web CI gate (mandatory before push)

Pushes that touch `web/**` run **web-ci**: `lint` → `build` (includes `tsc`) → `typecheck` → `test`.  
**Most failed pushes** are either ESLint `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect` or TypeScript errors that only show up in `next build` / `tsc` — not in the editor alone.

## Before commit or push (when `web/` changed)

```bash
cd web
npm run lint
npm run typecheck
# or: npm run build   # catches the same tsc errors CI hits
npm test             # when you changed components or tests
```

Do **not** commit/push web changes until lint + typecheck **and the full test suite** are clean (`pnpm test` / `npm test` — not only the files you touched). A green subset still fails web-ci.

---

## Failure pattern 1 — `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`

Do **not** call `setState` synchronously inside `useEffect` to mirror props/state.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
useEffect(() => {
  setOpportunity(initial);
}, [initial]);
```

| Situation | Fix |
|-----------|-----|
| Sync prop → local state | During-render: `if (prop !== synced) { setSynced(prop); setLocal(prop); }` |
| Derived display | `useMemo` — no effect |
| Reset on identity change | `key={id}` remount |

---

## Failure pattern 2 — `ApiResult` `.error` after a boolean helper

`ApiResult<T>` is a discriminated union. `.error` exists only on `{ ok: false }`.  
A helper that returns `boolean` (e.g. `applyDetailResult(result)`) does **not** narrow `result` for TypeScript — even after an early return on success.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fails next build / tsc
if (applyDetailResult(result)) {
  toast.success("Saved");
  return;
}
toast.error(codeMessage(result.error)); // Property 'error' does not exist on ok:true

// ✅ GOOD — narrow explicitly
if (applyDetailResult(result)) {
  toast.success("Saved");
  return;
}
if (!result.ok) toast.error(codeMessage(result.error));

// ✅ ALSO GOOD — check ok first (narrows naturally)
if (result.ok) {
  /* use result.data */
  return;
}
toast.error(codeMessage(result.error));
```

Same rule for `patchMutation.data.error` — guard with `!data.ok` first.

---

## Agent checklist

1. After editing `web/**`, run **lint**, **typecheck**, and **full `npm test` / `pnpm test`** (not lint alone; not a single test file alone).
2. Scan new `useEffect` bodies for synchronous `setX(`.
3. Scan `codeMessage(….error)` / `result.error` — ensure `!result.ok` (or `if (result.ok)` early return) is in scope.
4. If you change Save/blur/async flows, update any detail-client tests that mock `@/lib/app-api/client` so new client calls (`postMmrVin`, etc.) resolve.
5. Only then commit/push.
